question:
Let P = {x : x is a prime number, x < 10}\nQ = {x : x is an even natural number}\nR = {x : x is a perfect square, x < 10}\nS = {x : x is a natural number that divides 12}\nWhich of the following is true?
(a) Q ∩ S = {2, 4, 6, 12}
(b) P ∩ R = ∅
(c) P ∪ Q = {2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 12, ...}
(d) R ∩ S = {1, 4}
